# SEO and Analytics Guidelines

## SEO Best Practices
Implement SEO optimization for better search engine visibility and user experience.

## Meta Tags and Metadata
Use Next.js metadata API in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx):
```typescript
export const metadata = {
  title: 'Company Name - Main Value Proposition',
  description: 'Clear, compelling description of what the company does (150-160 characters)',
  keywords: 'relevant, keywords, for, your, industry',
  openGraph: {
    title: 'Company Name - Main Value Proposition',
    description: 'Description for social media sharing',
    images: ['/og-image.jpg'],
  },
  twitter: {
    card: 'summary_large_image',
    title: 'Company Name - Main Value Proposition',
    description: 'Description for Twitter sharing',
    images: ['/twitter-image.jpg'],
  },
}
```

## Page Structure for SEO
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)
- Include relevant keywords naturally in content
- Add alt text to all images
- Use descriptive URLs for pages

## Content Optimization
- Write compelling, keyword-rich content
- Include relevant keywords in headings and subheadings
- Use internal linking to connect related content
- Optimize images with descriptive filenames and alt text
- Include schema markup for structured data

## Technical SEO
- Ensure fast loading times (optimize images, minimize CSS/JS)
- Make the site mobile-friendly (responsive design)
- Implement proper URL structure
- Add XML sitemap
- Configure robots.txt file
- Use canonical URLs to prevent duplicate content

## Analytics Implementation
Consider implementing analytics tools:
- Google Analytics 4 for user behavior tracking
- Google Search Console for SEO monitoring
- Hotjar or similar for user experience insights
- Conversion tracking for form submissions and CTAs

## Performance Monitoring
- Use Lighthouse for performance audits
- Monitor Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)
- Track page load times
- Monitor mobile performance
- Regular SEO audits and updates

## Local SEO (if applicable)
- Include business address and contact information
- Add Google My Business integration
- Include local keywords in content
- Add location-specific landing pages
- Implement local schema markup
